body.description: Product Description The Ride on Wiggle Car by Lil’ Rider is a great way to keep kids active and will surely become your child’s preferred method of transportation! Wiggle Car by Lil’ Rider is a safe, easy to operate, ride on toy that doesn’t require gears, pedals or batteries for a smooth, quiet and fun activity for your child. Constructed of durable plastic, this Wiggle Car will provide miles of enjoyment for kids over three years old, simply twist, wiggle, and go. From the Manufacturer Looking for a children's toy that will delight, fascinate, and invigorate for years to come? Come to the rescue with the perfect toy: The revolutionary new Lil' Rider Wiggle car. It's like magic, but you don't need to be a magician to get it to work. The Lil' Rider? Wiggle car is a mechanical marvel that makes use of that most inexhaustible of energy sources, kid-power, by harnessing the natural forces of inertia, centrifugal force, gravity, and friction. It's so easy to operate; all it needs is a driver and a smooth, flat surface. It doesn't require an expensive power source that needs constant replacement. No batteries, no power-cells, no liquid fuel-just the occasional cookie or two. It's quiet too-the only sound you'll hear is the sound of its wheels. It provides kids with plenty of exercise, more so than most toys. And the Lil' Rider? Wiggle car is engineered to be absolutely safe when used appropriately.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Wiggle Toddler Car for Ages 3+ Encourage kids to be active indoors or out with this fun wiggle scooter, which is constructed from durable plastic with no gears, batteries, or pedals. Your little one can simply twist, wiggle, and go in this kids ride on car, for a smooth, quiet, and entertaining activity that provides year-round fun for ages 3 and up.

Wiggle Toddler Car for Ages 3+ Encourage kids to be active indoors or out with this fun wiggle scooter, which is constructed from durable plastic with no gears, batteries, or pedals. Your little one can simply twist, wiggle, and go in this kids ride on car, for a smooth, quiet, and entertaining activity that provides year-round fun for ages 3 and up.

Indoor or Outdoor Toy All your child needs to get moving in this wiggle car ride on toy is a smooth, flat surface, either indoors or out. Appropriate riding surfaces include linoleum, concrete, asphalt, or tile. Note: the Lil Rider Wiggle Car is not recommended for use on wood floors, and is intended to be used under the direct supervision of an adult.

Safe and Durable Construction This wiggle bike is made from rugged, high-quality plastics that are free of banned phthalates and durable enough to hold up to 110-pounds of weight, for season after season of safe, active fun. These toddler riding toys are also safety tested and provide healthy exercise because they are kid-powered rather than battery-powered.

Helps Develop Motor Skills In addition to encouraging physical activity both indoors and outside, toddler riding toys like this wiggle car help your little rider develop and refine their gross motor skills like balancing, coordination, and steering while also encouraging your child to be active and independent while they pretend play that they are driving a car just like mom or dad.

reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Handle impossible to get secured in place.
reviews.reviewText: There are several points I’m going to make about why this is getting returned but I’ll start with the one that renders it impossible to use.I’m very adept at putting things together and following instructions. While it appears from some reviews that theirs came with the rubber mallet that the instructions say is critical; ours did NOT come with that. Luckily I have just about every kind of tool including my own set of socket wrenches which I hoped would resolve the fact that the little metal tool they included did NOTHING to tighten the bolt on the steering wheel.Despite having better tools for the job, the bolt wouldn’t tighten at all and no matter what we do the handle comes right off every time. I’m not putting my 3 year old grandchild on this. When my kids were young we had the REAL plasma car which they loved and have all talked about it being a favorite from childhood. Will be returning this and getting a plasmacar.Lots of reviews indicated the handle comes off and unfortunately I didn’t see those until I came back looking for any solution to get this thing put together. They also indicate problems with the wheels (we wouldn’t know as we did not get to that point of use). Some even indicate that the wheels that come with it don’t work but that they got the “upgraded wheels” and installed them and they’re great. I personally don’t feel like buying upgraded wheels should be necessary for it to work right. Also, people who got two at the same time mention one being able to be put together and the other they could not.But I am curious why some people seem to be able to get the handle to attach while others don’t. To me that indicates that there is not uniformity in these products and you don’t know what you’re going to get… so don’t bother.
